	quests: [
		{
			dependencies: []
			description: [
				"This pack includes a suite of RPG class mods centered on the §6Arsenal RPG Series§r."
				""
				"§bWizards§r cast elemental spells using wands and staves. §bPaladins \u0026 Priests§r wield divine power through hammers, maces, and holy wands. §bRogues \u0026 Warriors§r master agile and crushing combat styles. §bArchers§r unlock a full archery skill tree usable with any bow or crossbow."
				""
				"All classes require a §6Spell Binding Table§r to unlock their skill books. These tables are found in §eGazebo§r structures \u2014 open-air village structures added by the §bGazebos§r mod. Each class has its own village structure type: Wizard Towers, Sanctuaries, Archery Ranges, and Barracks."
				""
				"§6Runes§r (added by the §bRunes§r mod) act as ammunition for spells \u2014 like arrows for bows. Stock them before casting."
				""
				"§bJewelry§r adds gem-set rings and necklaces found in the world or crafted at a Jeweler's Kit. §bArsenal§r adds 40+ legendary weapons that only drop from end-game bosses."
			]
			icon: "wizards:wand_novice"
			id: "9000"
			optional: true
			size: 1.5d
			subtitle: "Click to learn more"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9100"
				title: "RPG Classes Overview"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "\u2764 RPG Classes"
			x: 0.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9000"]
			description: [
				"§bGazebos§r adds open-air village structures that contain §6Spell Binding Tables§r for all RPG class mods."
				""
				"Different village types house different classes:"
				"\u2022 §eArchery Range§r \u2014 Archers"
				"\u2022 §eSanctuary / Temple§r \u2014 Paladins \u0026 Priests"
				"\u2022 §eWizard Tower§r \u2014 Wizards"
				"\u2022 §eBarracks§r \u2014 Rogues \u0026 Warriors"
				""
				"Finding one of these structures and interacting with the Spell Binding Table inside is the first step to unlocking any class skill book."
			]
			icon: "archers:archers_workbench"
			id: "9002"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9102"
				title: "Find a Gazebo village structure"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "The Village Specialist"
			subtitle: "Every class begins in a village"
			x: 2.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9000"]
			description: [
				"§bRunes§r are the ammunition for all class spell casting in the §6Arsenal RPG Series§r."
				""
				"Just as bows require arrows, wands and spell books require Runes to cast. Craft them early and keep a stock in your inventory at all times."
				""
				"Without Runes, your spell abilities will fizzle regardless of what skill book or wand you carry. The §6Spell Infinity§r enchantment (Wizards) eliminates this cost once unlocked."
			]
			id: "9003"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9103"
				title: "Craft some Runes to use as spell ammunition"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Runic Fuel"
			subtitle: "The currency of power"
			x: 0.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9000"]
			description: [
				"§bJewelry§r adds over 25 rings and necklaces crafted from gemstones and precious metals."
				""
				"§6Gem Veins§r spawn at diamond depth \u2014 roughly half as common as diamonds. Gems come in six varieties:"
				"\u2022 §cRuby§r \u2022 §aJade§r \u2022 §6Citrine§r \u2022 §9Sapphire§r \u2022 §eTopaz§r \u2022 §5Tanzanite§r"
				""
				"Mine a gem vein underground to collect your first gem. The §6Jeweler\u2019s Kit§r is needed to craft rings and necklaces."
			]
			icon: "jewelry:ruby"
			id: "9004"
			tasks: [{
				id: "9104"
				item: "jewelry:ruby"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "First Gem"
			subtitle: "Something precious from the deep"
			rewards: [{
				id: "9204"
				item: "jewelry:jewelers_kit"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -2.0d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["9004"]
			description: [
				"Craft rings and necklaces at the §6Jeweler\u2019s Kit§r by combining gems with Gold or Netherite ingots."
				""
				"Each piece provides unique stat bonuses \u2014 attack damage, speed, defense, and more. Higher-tier gems and materials yield stronger bonuses."
				""
				"§eJeweler§r villagers (found in villages) sell low-to-mid tier pieces. Unique, powerful pieces can be found in §cEnd City§r and §cAncient City§r loot."
			]
			icon: "jewelry:copper_ring"
